   "source": [
    "# NumCompute-Stream Demo: Streaming Decision Trees and Ensembles\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates the `numcompute_stream` package in a streaming machine-learning setting.\n",
    "\n",
    "It shows how to:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Load a CSV file using the custom `io.py` module.\n",
    "2. Split the dataset into chunks to simulate streaming data.\n",
    "3. Train a single decision tree incrementally using `partial_fit()`.\n",
    "4. Train an ensemble model incrementally using `partial_fit()`.\n",
    "5. Log chunk-level accuracy, cumulative accuracy and memory usage.\n",
    "6. Visualise streaming metric trends using `visualise.py`.\n",
    "\n",
    "Only Python, NumPy and matplotlib are used.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "a9c01138",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Project root: D:\\Tuitor Drive\\May\\Assignment\\NumCompute-Stream\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Make imports work when this notebook is opened from the demo/ folder.\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "PROJECT_ROOT = Path.cwd()\n",
    "if PROJECT_ROOT.name == \"demo\":\n",
    "    PROJECT_ROOT = PROJECT_ROOT.parent\n",
    "\n",
    "if str(PROJECT_ROOT) not in sys.path:\n",
    "    sys.path.insert(0, str(PROJECT_ROOT))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Project root:\", PROJECT_ROOT)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "19c16571",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "from numcompute_stream.io import read_csv, chunk_iter, write_csv\n",
    "from numcompute_stream.preprocessing import Imputer, StandardScaler\n",
    "from numcompute_stream.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier\n",
    "from numcompute_stream.ensemble import EnsembleClassifier\n",
    "from numcompute_stream.pipeline import Pipeline\n",
    "from numcompute_stream.stream import StreamTrainer\n",
    "from numcompute_stream.metrics import (\n",
    "    StreamingAccuracy,\n",
    "    StreamingPrecision,\n",
    "    StreamingRecall,\n",
    "    StreamingF1,\n",
    "    StreamingClassificationMetrics,\n",
    ")\n",
    "from numcompute_stream.visualise import (\n",
    "    plot_metric_over_time,\n",
    "    compare_models,\n",
    "    plot_predictions_vs_ground_truth,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "np.set_printoptions(precision=4, suppress=True)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b1f2f1ed",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Create or Load the Demo CSV Dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "The assignment requires the demo to load a dataset from a CSV file using the custom `io.py` pipeline.  \n",
    "This cell creates `demo/sample_data.csv` only if it does not already exist.\n",
    "\n",
    "The dataset is a simple binary classification dataset with:\n",
    "\n",
    "- 300 samples\n",
    "- 6 numeric features\n",
    "- binary target labels: `0` and `1`\n",
    "- a small number of missing values to test the streaming `Imputer`\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "ac8f643a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Using existing dataset: D:\\Tuitor Drive\\May\\Assignment\\NumCompute-Stream\\demo\\sample_data.csv\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "demo_path = PROJECT_ROOT / \"demo\"\n",
    "demo_path.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "csv_path = demo_path / \"sample_data.csv\"\n",
    "\n",
    "if not csv_path.exists():\n",
    "    rng = np.random.default_rng(42)\n",
    "    n_samples = 300\n",
    "    n_features = 6\n",
    "\n",
    "    X_generated = rng.normal(0.0, 1.0, size=(n_samples, n_features))\n",
    "    weights = np.array([1.4, -1.1, 0.8, 0.4, -0.7, 0.6])\n",
    "    noise = rng.normal(0.0, 0.35, size=n_samples)\n",
    "\n",
    "    score = X_generated @ weights + noise\n",
    "    y_generated = (score > np.median(score)).astype(int)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Add missing values to test the custom Imputer.\n",
    "    missing_mask = rng.random(X_generated.shape) < 0.04\n",
    "    X_generated[missing_mask] = np.nan\n",
    "\n",
    "    header = [f\"feature_{i+1}\" for i in range(n_features)] + [\"target\"]\n",
    "    write_csv(csv_path, X_generated, y_generated, header=header)\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(\"Created demo dataset:\", csv_path)\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"Using existing dataset:\", csv_path)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "547cb082",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "X shape: (300, 6)\n",
      "y shape: (300,)\n",
      "Classes: [0 1]\n",
      "Missing values in X: 72\n",
      "First 5 rows of X:\n",
      "[[ 0.3047 -1.04    0.7505     nan -1.951  -1.3022]\n",
      " [ 0.1278 -0.3162 -0.0168 -0.853   0.8794  0.7778]\n",
      " [ 0.066   1.1272  0.4675 -0.8593  0.3688 -0.9589]\n",
      " [ 0.8784 -0.0499 -0.1849 -0.6809  1.2225 -0.1545]\n",
      " [-0.4283 -0.3521  0.5323  0.3654  0.4127  0.4308]]\n",
      "First 10 labels: [1 1 0 0 1 1 1 0 1 1]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "X, y = read_csv(csv_path, target_column=-1, skip_header=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"X shape:\", X.shape)\n",
    "print(\"y shape:\", y.shape)\n",
    "print(\"Classes:\", np.unique(y))\n",
    "print(\"Missing values in X:\", np.isnan(X).sum())\n",
    "print(\"First 5 rows of X:\")\n",
    "print(X[:5])\n",
    "print(\"First 10 labels:\", y[:10])\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e8e1335f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Split the Dataset into Streaming Chunks\n",
    "\n",
    "Instead of training the model once on the full dataset, the data is processed in chunks.  \n",
    "This simulates a real-time data stream where new records arrive gradually.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "c7a5755d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Number of chunks: 10\n",
      "Chunk size: 30\n",
      "First chunk X shape: (30, 6)\n",
      "First chunk y shape: (30,)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "chunk_size = 30\n",
    "chunks = list(chunk_iter(X, y, chunk_size=chunk_size, shuffle=False))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Number of chunks:\", len(chunks))\n",
    "print(\"Chunk size:\", chunk_size)\n",
    "print(\"First chunk X shape:\", chunks[0][0].shape)\n",
    "print(\"First chunk y shape:\", chunks[0][1].shape)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7b993abd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Build a Streaming Single-Tree Pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "The first model uses:\n",
    "\n",
    "- `Imputer()` for missing-value handling\n",
    "- `StandardScaler()` for incremental scaling\n",
    "- `DecisionTreeClassifier()` for streaming tree-based classification\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "6db3ccf3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Single-tree pipeline ready.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "tree_pipeline = Pipeline([\n",
    "    (\"imputer\", Imputer()),\n",
    "    (\"scaler\", StandardScaler()),\n",
    "    (\"model\", DecisionTreeClassifier(\n",
    "        max_depth=5,\n",
    "        min_samples_split=4,\n",
    "        criterion=\"gini\",\n",
    "        random_state=42,\n",
    "        max_samples=1000\n",
    "    )),\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "tree_trainer = StreamTrainer(\n",
    "    pipeline=tree_pipeline,\n",
    "    metrics={\n",
    "        \"accuracy\": StreamingAccuracy(),\n",
    "        \"precision\": StreamingPrecision(labels=[0, 1]),\n",
    "        \"recall\": StreamingRecall(labels=[0, 1]),\n",
    "        \"f1\": StreamingF1(labels=[0, 1]),\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    evaluate_before_fit=False,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Single-tree pipeline ready.\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8337bf2e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Train the Single Tree Incrementally\n",
    "\n",
    "Each chunk is passed into `fit_chunk()`.  \n",
    "Internally, this calls the pipeline's `partial_fit()` method and records streaming metrics.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "54e6af23",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Chunk 01 | chunk accuracy=1.000 | cumulative accuracy=1.000 | memory=11.2 KB\n",
      "Chunk 02 | chunk accuracy=0.967 | cumulative accuracy=0.983 | memory=15.5 KB\n",
      "Chunk 03 | chunk accuracy=0.967 | cumulative accuracy=0.978 | memory=20.1 KB\n",
      "Chunk 04 | chunk accuracy=0.933 | cumulative accuracy=0.967 | memory=24.7 KB\n",
      "Chunk 05 | chunk accuracy=1.000 | cumulative accuracy=0.973 | memory=28.9 KB\n",
      "Chunk 06 | chunk accuracy=1.000 | cumulative accuracy=0.978 | memory=33.0 KB\n",
      "Chunk 07 | chunk accuracy=1.000 | cumulative accuracy=0.981 | memory=36.8 KB\n",
      "Chunk 08 | chunk accuracy=0.967 | cumulative accuracy=0.979 | memory=40.5 KB\n",
      "Chunk 09 | chunk accuracy=0.933 | cumulative accuracy=0.974 | memory=44.2 KB\n",
      "Chunk 10 | chunk accuracy=0.867 | cumulative accuracy=0.963 | memory=47.9 KB\n",
      "Final single-tree cumulative accuracy: 0.9633333333333334\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "for i, (X_chunk, y_chunk) in enumerate(chunks, start=1):\n",
    "    log = tree_trainer.fit_chunk(X_chunk, y_chunk)\n",
    "    print(\n",
    "        f\"Chunk {i:02d} | \"\n",
    "        f\"chunk accuracy={log['chunk_accuracy']:.3f} | \"\n",
    "        f\"cumulative accuracy={log['cumulative_accuracy']:.3f} | \"\n",
    "        f\"memory={log['memory_bytes'] / 1024:.1f} KB\"\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "tree_logs = tree_trainer.logs()\n",
    "tree_accuracy = [row[\"cumulative_accuracy\"] for row in tree_logs]\n",
    "tree_chunk_accuracy = [row[\"chunk_accuracy\"] for row in tree_logs]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Final single-tree cumulative accuracy:\", tree_accuracy[-1])\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "af2bed03",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Build a Streaming Ensemble Pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "The second model uses an ensemble of decision trees.  \n",
    "This satisfies the assignment requirement for a tree-based ensemble method.\n",
    "\n",
    "The ensemble uses:\n",
    "\n",
    "- multiple decision trees\n",
    "- bootstrap sampling\n",
    "- random-feature selection through `method=\"random_forest\"`\n",
    "- majority voting for prediction\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "611144ad",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Ensemble pipeline ready.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ensemble_pipeline = Pipeline([\n",
    "    (\"imputer\", Imputer()),\n",
    "    (\"scaler\", StandardScaler()),\n",
    "    (\"model\", EnsembleClassifier(\n",
    "        n_estimators=7,\n",
    "        method=\"random_forest\",\n",
    "        max_depth=5,\n",
    "        min_samples_split=4,\n",
    "        criterion=\"gini\",\n",
    "        bootstrap=True,\n",
    "        sample_fraction=0.9,\n",
    "        random_state=42,\n",
    "        max_samples=1000\n",
    "    )),\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "ensemble_trainer = StreamTrainer(\n",
    "    pipeline=ensemble_pipeline,\n",
    "    metrics={\n",
    "        \"accuracy\": StreamingAccuracy(),\n",
    "        \"precision\": StreamingPrecision(labels=[0, 1]),\n",
    "        \"recall\": StreamingRecall(labels=[0, 1]),\n",
    "        \"f1\": StreamingF1(labels=[0, 1]),\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    evaluate_before_fit=False,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Ensemble pipeline ready.\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d1592684",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Train the Ensemble Incrementally\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "c84b6d49",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
